                    "company": "LDE Centre for Sustainability",
                    "description": "The University of Leiden, the Technical University of Delft and the Erasmus University Rotterdam have set up an L-D-E collaboration encompassing around 8 joint research centers. One of them focuses on sustainability, and given the strengths of these universities this Centre for Sustainability focuses on resource-efficiency and the circular economy. The CfS combines the unique strengths of Leiden University-CML in material flow analysis, LCA and input-output analysis, TU Delft in sustainable product design (being a pioneer university with the Ellen MacArthur Foundation), materials technology, and technology, policy and society, and the EURs Faculties of Economics, Social Sciences and the Rotterdam School of Management (with senior staff closely connected to the World Business Council for Sustainable Development). CfS is chaired by a board of professors and supervised by a Steering committee of Deans, and combines the capacities of some 70 permanent staff plus many more PhDs and post-docs in this field across the three universities.",
